_rawConfigs.promotionTitle: Save up to 35% on additional pairs
_rawConfigs.termsText:
Purchase multiple pairs of eyeglasses (frame & prescription lenses) to get 20% off each additional pair of glasses after your first order. Multiple qualifying glasses must be purchased during a single online transaction. Qualifying purchases include: a complete pair of prescription eyeglasses (frame & prescription lenses) or an insurance order for a complete pair of glasses. Insurance benefits should be maximized on the first order (if applicable).

Discounts must be applied to qualifying orders that are of equal or lesser value. For 35% off, purchase a complete pair of sunglasses in addition to a second complete pair. Qualifying purchases include any prescription polarized or non-polarized sun lens & frame purchase. The least expensive pair(s) will receive the 35% discount.

genAiDetails.genAiDescription: The Apple iPad Pro features a  10.5-inch Retina display  with 2224 x 1668 resolution, powered by the A10X Fusion chip. It has a  12MP main camera , 7MP FaceTime HD camera, and  256GB storage with 4GB RAM . The device measures 9.8 inches in height, 6.8 inches in width, and 0.24 inches in depth, weighing 1.03 lbs. It supports Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 4.2, and has a  built-in 30.4-watt-hour rechargeable battery , providing  up to 10 hours of web surfing or video watching . The bundle includes a case, pre-installed tempered glass, rapid charger, and Bluetooth airbuds.

customerReviews.reviewText: Everything works as it should. I love my I pad I use  it daily. I have had it for couple months now and have had no issues with it. I love that I got such a great deal on it. It had the most updated operating system too.
customerReviews.reviewTitle: Don't be afraid of open box deals!

customerReviews.reviewText: Due to the larger size and thinness of laptop made it a little difficult to hang on to. I'm hoping with a cover it will be more comfortable to hang on to. Also did not specify what generation is was which hampers my ability to order the correct cover.

I was excited when the box came with my ipad. However, it was the wrong one. I took it back to Walmart. I couldn't return it there. So, I called 1-800-WALMART. They sent a text to the vendor. (It was, of course, Friday afternoon.) On Monday, I got a text from the vendor and a return label. I took the box to a FedEx dropoff location. For some reason, they could not read the label I printed. I went back to the FedEx dropoff location. I couldn't print or send a text there. (Can't imagine a Fedex dropoff that can't do that. Their network was closed, she said. So, I went home and sent an email from there. The package is on-its-way. Expect delivery Monday. Then the vendor said they would exchange the item and send it to me. I hope it works.

I ordered this iPad and a different, older model that doesn't update to the latest iOS was sent. I reached out and requested the model ordered be sent. The seller refused to respond and when I questioned Walmart they said it was a third party and they had nothing to do with it. The item was sold through Walmart, step and be responsible for what you are advertising and selling under your Walmart banner. All I wanted was the model I purchased and it is still showing available online but at a higher price now.
customerReviews.reviewTitle: Switch and bait and Walmart approved

customerReviews.reviewText: Receive the iPad with best shipping. Open the box examine the iPad. The screen cover was placed on. It seems to be the wrong size covers up. The camera hole may been put on incorrectly, but doesn't look to be the right size has a case on it. A case was never suggested in the purchase took the case off to find out the iPad, had several dents on the backside of it!!! iPad does seem to work

Wrong item was intentionally sent from the looks of other reviews. Ordered 256 GB ipad, received 64GB ipad.

 Before you decide to chance it, read my review. Bought the ipad Dec 9, received Dec 12, returned Dec 13. It is Feb 4 and I have yet to receive my refund. I have contacted Walmart two going on three times and the seller two times. Walmart states that they are waiting on a response from the seller. Walmart needs to ban this seller because it is making them look bad. I'm trying to be patient with Walmart but if they continue to allow bad sellers, such as this one, to stay on their platform then they need to be held accountable as well. 

I'd advise reading through all reviews under this product and the seller review before buying... or just dont buy. If possible, I will come back to update when I have my refund. Otherwise, I will be finding a way to sue. No one else should have to go through this.

The iPad started freezing up the second day I had it.  I contacted the protection plan I purchased and was told to contact Apple Care.  When I contacted Apple Care I was informed that the coverage expired.  But the associate tried for an hour over the phone to help me.  I found out that the iPad would not support any new updates.

Open Box says "like new." It is scratched, there is a line down the screen affecting the display. Not to mention the wrong item was sent. Was to be a 258gb and we received 64gb. Frustrating for  the cost of the purchase.

The back body have scratches on there  and screen has hair size scratch line , as committed it does not look like new or close to that .

Charger was shipped open

I can't get it to work and transfer my apps to it.
It does not have an apple back,  a  that I've had has an apple on the back.  I think it's a reject I would like to return it for a full refund Gail McAskin
